    <body>
        <p><i style="font-style: normal;">Description:</i> The permission mask of directories created by syslog-ng. Log directories are only created if a file after macro expansion refers to a non-existing directory, and directory creation is enabled (see also the <span class="Code">create-dirs()</span> option). For octal numbers prefix the number with <b class="Code">0</b>, for example, use <b class="Code">0755</b> for <b class="Code">rwxr-xr-x</b>.</p>
        <p>To preserve the original properties of an existing directory, use the option without specifying an attribute: <span class="Code">dir-perm()</span>. Note that when creating a new directory without specifying attributes for <span class="Code">dir-perm()</span>, the default permission of the directories is masked with the umask of the parent process (typically <b class="Code">0022</b>).</p>
    </body>
